%% Diagram: NRT refresh / flush / commit timeline
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant P as Primary Shard
    participant M as In-memory Buffer
    participant TL as Translog
    participant FC as Filesystem Cache
    participant D as Disk

    C->>P: Index doc
    P->>M: Append to buffer
    P->>TL: Append op (durable on fsync)
    P-->>C: ack

    Note over P,FC: Refresh (every 1s while index is active)
    P->>FC: Flush buffer as new searchable segment
    Note right of FC: Documents now visible to search

    Note over P,D: Flush (translog > 512MB or 30 min)
    P->>D: fsync segments to disk
    P->>TL: Truncate translog
    Note right of D: Durable Lucene commit

    Note over P,D: Crash recovery
    P->>D: Reopen committed segments
    P->>TL: Replay un-fsync'd ops
